{"questionId":"14507742","questionHtml":"<p>Find the size of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BV</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>VC</mi></math>&nbsp;AND&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use the cosine rule on triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BVC</mi></math>&nbsp;for any angle&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Recognition must be shown in context either in terms of labelled sides or side lengths.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cosB</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>…</mo><msup><mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>…</mo><mi>cosB</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>543314</mn><mo>…</mo></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>543</mn></math>&nbsp; </strong></em>(0.542 from 3 sf) (accept 31.1<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>let M be the midpoint of BC</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BM</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use sine or cosine in triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BMV</mi></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CMV</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arcsin</mi><mfrac><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>125</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>OR<em><strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>arccos</mi><mfrac><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>125</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>OR 0.271657<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 